lenders.name: Poverty2Prosperity.org Minh Nguyen2
lenders.loan_because: This is a Poverty2Prosperity.org Perpetual Lending account generously donated by Minh Nguyen. Poverty2Prosperity.org (P2P) engages in poverty alleviating projects. Our major project is to provide microloans through the Kiva platform. You can help support P2P by joining our lending team here: www.kiva.org/team/poverty2prosperity
lenders.occupational_info: This is the Minh Nguyen Perpetual Fund. P2P allows individuals to create a "Perpetual Fund" in their name that P2P manages on their behalf. Funds are locked into the account for permanent lending on Kiva. If you are interested in establishing a Perpetual Fund, please see our site for more information. P2P manages a number of funds including those targeted towards loans for women entrepreneurs, education & tuition fees, youth, and even personal housing. Please see our site for more details.

lenders.name: Rebecca
lenders.loan_because:
In 1985 I was an exchange student to Kenya, living in Mombasa and attending school there.  Although that was many years ago, I still feel an affinity for my host country, so predominantly make loans to Kenyans.

We have very recently moved to a small property where we keep four chickens and are raising a calf.  My husband has started making our vegetable garden and we have plans for some other small-scale self-sufficiency.  

Generally we make loans based on some there being some affinity with our experiences/interests - so made loans to borrowers with agricultural aspirations, long before we had the opportunity to rent a farm of our own!
